  , issueCommentBody =
      "Instead of `feed_buffer_size` I propose `resume_size_limit`. The parameter is not feed-specific, since it works for arbitrary cursors. But it is resume-specific.\r\n\r\nI propose that the client and server use the same timeout.\r\n\r\nExponential backoff would be good. The user can specify the first retry interval, and it will increase by a factor of 1.5 after that.\r\n\r\nSo the optargs would be `resume_time_limit`, `resume_size_limit`, `resume_initial_retry_interval`."
